      • getMask

        public String getMask(Float value)
        Method that returns the string mask for missing values of type float. Unlike the extended missing value types for whole numbers, floating point missing values are defined by a range of possible floating point values. The range can be expressed roughly as n_[1] = [n_[1], n_[2]) or the minimum value for the extended missing value up to - but excluding - the next extended missing value.
        Parameters:
        value - A Float value for which the mask should be returned
        Returns:
        A string containing the extended missing value mask
